<subsection xml:id="subsec-back-bearing">
    <title>Back Bearing</title>
    <definition xml:id="def-back-bearing">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <alert>Back bearing</alert> refers to the direction <em>opposite</em> to the direction of a given bearing. 
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>
     <p>
        <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        If the <alert>fore bearing</alert> (the <em>bearing</em> from <alert>point A</alert> to <alert>point B</alert>)
         is known, the <alert>back bearing</alert> (from <alert>point B</alert> to <alert>point A</alert>) 
        can be calculated by <em>adding</em> or <em>subtracting</em> <m>180^\circ</m> depending on the value of the fore bearing.
    </p>
    <p>
        For example, if the fore bearing is <em>less</em> than <m>180^\circ</m>, the back bearing is found by <em>adding</em> <m>180^\circ</m>. 
        If the fore bearing is <em>greater</em> than <m>180^\circ</m>, the back bearing is found by <em>subtracting</em> <m>180^\circ</m>.
    </p>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                The bearing of <alert>Town A</alert> from <alert>Town B</alert> is <m>045^\circ</m>. 
                Find the bearing of <alert>Town B</alert> from <alert>Town A</alert>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                To find the bearing of <alert>Town B</alert> from <alert>Town A</alert>, 
                we need to determine the direction from <alert>Town A</alert> back to <alert>Town B</alert>.
            </p>

            <p>
                Since the bearing of <alert>Town A</alert> from <alert>Town B</alert> is <alert>less than </alert> 
                <m>180^\circ</m>, then to find <alert>Town B</alert> from <alert>Town A</alert> we add <m>180^\circ</m> to the original bearing:
            </p>

            <p>
                <m>
                    045^\circ + 180^\circ = 225^\circ
                </m>
            </p>
            <image source="bearing-image.png" width="50%">
                <shortdescription>Bearing from Town A to Town B</shortdescription>
            </image>
            <p>
                Therefore, the bearing of <alert>Town B</alert> from <alert>Town A</alert> is <m>225^\circ</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
